# Local-only env. Never commit; never package.
#
# Files merge convention (matches BXM/UJM):
#   The "Default Values" section is overwritten on every `npx mgr setup`.
#   The "Custom Values" section is preserved verbatim — put your secrets there.
#   Existing values for keys that appear in both sections stay in their original section.
#   Values are normalized to double-quoted form on every merge (handles spaces / special chars).

# ========== Default Values ==========

# ─── GitHub ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GH_TOKEN=""

# ─── Backend Manager ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BACKEND_MANAGER_KEY=""

# ─── macOS signing + notarization ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Point CSC_LINK at build/certs/developer-id-application.p12 (per-brand cert file).
# See docs/signing.md or build/certs/README.md for full setup.
CSC_LINK=""
CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=""

# Notarization (App Store Connect API key)
APPLE_API_KEY=""
APPLE_API_KEY_ID=""
APPLE_API_ISSUER=""
APPLE_TEAM_ID=""

# ─── Windows signing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Signing strategy is set in config/electron-manager.json (`signing.windows.strategy`):
# self-hosted (default) | cloud | local. The runner box / signtool credentials live
# on the runner machine itself, not in the consumer's .env.

# Cloud-signing provider (only when signing.windows.strategy=cloud).
WIN_CLOUD_SIGN_PROVIDER=""

# ========== Custom Values ==========

# Anything below this line is yours and won't be touched by `npx mgr setup`.
